**You will need to install the included extDB first prior to this install.
extDB instructions are included.**

**Mission side**
1. Add the scripts folder to your MP Mission (Map name) folder.
   Or add the starter_kit folder (in the scripts folder) to your existing scripts folder

2. In the init file paste:

	execVM "scripts\starter_kit\player_login.sqf";
	
under: 	

if (DZE_R3F_WEIGHT) then {execVM "\z\addons\dayz_code\external\R3F_Realism\R3F_Realism_Init.sqf";};

4. Add:

		//Starter Kit
		["Smartphone_DZE","Starter Kit","execVM 'scripts\starter_kit\player_starterkit.sqf';","true"]
		
to the DZE_CLICK_ACTIONS section on the configVariables.sqf.
** If this will be the last entry, remove the last comma after true.
You can use a radio or any item you wish.

**Server side**
5. Go to your dayz_server folder, navigate to init/server_functions.sqf and find:

 "extDB" callExtension "9:LOCK";

under that paste:

/*Starter Kit*/
	fn_async =	compile preprocessFileLineNumbers "\z\addons\dayz_server\compile\starterkit\fn_async.sqf";
	server_queryStartKit = 		compile preprocessFileLineNumbers "\z\addons\dayz_server\compile\starterkit\server_queryStartKit.sqf";
	server_claimstartkit = 		compile preprocessFileLineNumbers "\z\addons\dayz_server\compile\starterkit\server_claimstartkit.sqf";
	"PVDZE_ClaimStartKit" 	addPublicVariableEventHandler {(_this select 1) spawn server_claimstartkit;	};
	"PVDZE_queryStartKit" 	addPublicVariableEventHandler {(_this select 1) spawn server_queryStartKit;	};
	
6. Add the starterkit folder(found in the included server folder) to your dayz_server\compile folder.

7. Complete! You can edit the kit loadout in scripts/starter_kit/player_starterkit.sqf
look for: _crateMags = [. **Pay special attention to the code flow**